Defendant in custody.   
Count 1 - Conspiracy to Commit Robbery with Threat of Force - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of fifty-two (52) months.   Twenty-eight (28) months initial confinement followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
2) Pay restitution of $2,500.00 to KK Unimart; $254.00 to Delores Kuik and $662.78 to Shoreline Credit Union;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Submit DNA sample; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
7) Not to be on or near the premise of KK Mobile Gas Station in Mishicot, WI 54228;
8) Defendant's prison wages may be garnished during her prison time to pay restitution.   
Count 2 - Furnishing a Firearm to an Unauthorized Person - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years consecutive to count 1.   Conditions of probation are same as count 1.   
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given credit for 307 days time already served.   
Minutes.
